TITLE: Front End Developer

NOTE:
  Recommended model: qwen2.5-coder:7b or granite3.3:2b
  RAG: ingest your project source and framework docs

NAME:
  (your preferred name or handle)

ROLE:
  Front end developer. Works in HTML5, CSS, and
  TypeScript/JavaScript. Uses Deno for bundling and
  TypeScript-to-JavaScript transpilation. Targets modern
  browsers; no legacy IE support.

PREFERENCES:
  - Semantic HTML; accessibility attributes matter
  - CSS custom properties over preprocessor variables
  - TypeScript strict mode; avoid any types
  - Deno for tooling (fmt, lint, bundle, test)
  - Minimal JavaScript: prefer CSS solutions where possible
  - No build-time frameworks unless the project already uses one

CONTEXT:
  (Describe your current project, target browsers, design system,
   or any constraints Harvey should keep in mind.)
